definition: to sign one's name/visa/variant of 籤|签[qian1]

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc

sentences.english: Similarly, suppose you want to do a checkout on a document.
sentences.chinese: 類似地，假設您想在一個文檔上執行一個簽出操作。

sentences.english: You may need to check out the Actions before you can edit them.
sentences.chinese: 您可能需要首先簽出操作，然後才能對其進行編輯。

sentences.english: If you are checking out a branch, that branch becomes your working branch.
sentences.chinese: 如果簽出一個分支，則該分支將成爲工作分支。

sentences.english: Once it is authenticated, it checks out the code from SVN repository.
sentences.chinese: 一旦通過驗證，就會簽出文件倉庫中的代碼。

sentences.english: Overwrite writable files that are not checked out to allow the system to overwrite existing files.
sentences.chinese: “覆蓋未簽出的可寫文件”以允許系統覆蓋現有文件。

sentences.english: You need to sign the student out.
sentences.chinese: 您必須在簽名簿上將他們簽出。

sentences.english: Compare the latest version on the server to the version checked out to you.
sentences.chinese: 比較伺服器上的最新版本與已簽出給您的版本。

sentences.english: Compare the copy in your workspace to the version on the server that is checked out to you.
sentences.chinese: 比較工作區中的複本與伺服器上已簽出給您的版本。

sentences.english: A check-in lock is less restrictive than a check-out lock.
sentences.chinese: 簽入鎖的限制少於簽出鎖。

definition: toss a peach, get back a plum (idiom); to return a favor/to exchange gifts/Scratch my back, and I'll scratch yours.

a tax declaration form/a tax return
